24/05/2011
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Police conducted a large anti-corruption operation Monday (May 23rd), searching the homes of dozens of customs officials in Bucharest and Constanta on suspicion of smuggling and tax evasion.
Laurentiu Mironescu, secretary-general of the Interior Ministry, was detained for questioning.
He was later sacked by the ministry.
According to media reports, Mironescu and his business partner -- Democratic Liberal Senator Mircea Banias -- have caused 1m euros in damages to the state through tax evasion involving petrol products.
(HotNews, Agerpres, Mediafax - 23/05/11)
